 found somewhaere to link it, ah well we live and learn) anyway, read it and tell me what you think. I've been working on it for quite some time now and I about have the plot straight. The whole thing is set now, in the same galaxy with no changes to Earth etc. That's enough from me...<br>
<br>
‘Frontier’ – Brief Setting:<br>
<br>
     0001 (Earth Calendar) the final battle of the “Aeon Wars” now rages. Both the ‘Drahl’ and ‘Volation’ fleets along with their respective allies are locked into a battle to the death, whomever survives will at last have unchallenged dominion over the entire galaxy, on the side of light, the ‘Volations’ and on the side of dark the ‘Drahl’.<br>
     The two forces seem evenly matched but in a blinding flash the Blue Dwarf star of ‘Sinar’ implodes. All but the merest traces of the two fleets are left. Decimated, the remnants of the fleets withdraw to a shattered galaxy, torn apart by two centuries of war. What little remains of these two powerful, almost supernatural races, disappears into the fledgling civilisations dotted throughout the galaxy… The eternal stalemate continues.<br>
<br>
     1985 (Earth Calendar) the Imperium world of ‘Talbrai’ is about to fall to the ‘Kharn’, the forces of the ‘Darvin’ have fought well, but cut off from the rest of their Imperium, and thus all support, they cannot hold for much longer. <br>
Duke Brai, still commanding what little of his fleet remains from the flagship ‘Sonith’, gives the order for the rest of the royal family to flee to the nearby world of ‘Kiene’. <br>
     Time is short; soon ‘Kharn’ troops will be on ‘Talbrai’, the last of the imperial guard hurry the Duchess and her eldest son to one of the few Imperium vessels still left on ‘Talbrai’. Meanwhile in orbit the Imperial Cruiser ‘Kahadrim’ with the youngest of the Duke sons aboard, is under attack, its shields failing it sends out a general distress call… <br>
     An ion blast rips through the starboard side of the ‘Kahadrim’ killing much of her crew. As all appears lost another ship exits slipstream behind the ‘Kahadrim’. As it looms into view the light form the planet below allows it’s identification: “UNS Eros”; a UN ‘Sol Defence Federation’ vessel, an allay of the ‘Free-worlds’. Firing two shots across the bow of the attacking ‘Kharn’ ship it moves to assist the now mortally wounded Imperium vessel. <br>
     As three more ‘Kharn’ star-ships approach the Captain of the stricken vessel entrusts the safety of the Dukes son to the Human crew of the ‘Eros’ sending only ‘Hybara’ one of Duke Brai’s most trusted aids with him. <br>
     Knowing their destruction is imminent the ‘Kahadrim’ fires one more defiant volley at the ‘Kharn’ before she is cleaved in two by a spread of ITP’s – a parting gift from the ‘Kharn’. By this final act the crew of the ‘Kahadrim’ have allowed the escape of the ‘Eros’ and ensured the safety of Duke Brai’s youngest son.<br>
     Duke Brai is dead following the destruction of his ship the ‘Sonith’. The rest of the royal family has fled to ‘Kiene’, which although blockaded by the ‘Kharn’, is secure. That is all except the Dukes youngest son ‘Vilam’ who now speeds away aboard the ‘Eros’ toward the safety of the unsuspecting Earth.<br>
     ‘Talbrai’s’ fall marks the end of the “Sovereign Wars” and despite many such losses, a victory for the ‘Darvin Imperium’ over the ‘Kharn Empire’. The ‘Solt’ Treaty is signed and an uneasy peace once again pervades the galaxy.<br>
<br>
     1997, Earth is quiet and all it’s citizens carry on none the wiser to the situation developing in the galaxy around them and the efforts of the best kept secret in the world: the “United Nations Sol Defence Federation” dedicated to protecting the human race from threats it cannot begin to comprehend.<br>
     The pulses of war have once again shattered the clam of the galaxy. This time it is the ‘Free-worlds’ and the ‘UNSDF’ that must fight the ‘Kharn’, as the ‘Darvin Imperium’ are unwilling to break their hard won peace.<br>
     The Free-world alliance, of which the Federation is a member, now fights the Kharn across a vast region of space - along the borders of the ‘Free-worlds’ and the Kharn Empire, what is simply known as… the “Frontier”.<br>
<br>
     2001, for two years now the war with the Kharn has been reduced to little more than border skirmishes, the Frontier is quiet, too quiet. The ‘Kharn’ are up to something but at least for now the ‘Free-worlds’ are safe and those who live on the barren ‘Rim’ worlds at the edge of the ‘Free-world Alliance’ can try to carve out some sort of living. The ‘Rangers’; mandated by the ‘Solt’ treaty; enforce what little law there is and keep the ‘Rim-traders’ in line.<br>
     Even so the once formidable ‘Free-world Alliance’ has been reduced to a handful of member worlds forced to rely on the military force of the Federation and it’s crack “Star-Warrior” pilots to protect them.<br>
     A young Star-Warrior; Captain Will Reed; stands on the operations deck of ‘Centrum’ the Federation Fleet command centre, in orbit of Earth.<br>
     His past, cloudy, but his loyal and trusted friend “Bary” has trained him well. Only he knows all that the Imperium is unwilling to share: the truth about the ‘Kharn’ and their connection to the ‘Drahl’. The real stakes of the coming showdown with the ‘Kharn’, and more importantly what the ‘Darvin’ nobility really are and who and what he really is…<br>
<br>
